window.bookSummaryJSON = "Long Sunset is an intimate personal view of the sunset years of the former British Prime Minister, Winston Churchill. Anthony Montague Brown was Winston Churchill's private secretary from 1952 until his death in 1965. As the last member of what Churchill called \"my circle\" to have written his recollections, these memoirs shed much light on Churchill's activities and attitudes during his final decade. <p></p>"; 
